Installing VSCode.  

Installing Google Cloud CLI 

Installing Docker Desktop 

Setting up files in VSCode 

Setting up the DockerFile 

Building the image locally with the correct infrastructure I.e. amd64 

Uploading the image to GCR.  

Deploying the GCR image to Google Cloud Run via command line.  


gcloud config set project sound-helper-448209-a0 
gcloud auth configure-docker 
docker tag gradio-app gcr.io/sound-helper-448209-a0/gradio-app 

#Build the image locally with the correct infrastructure I.e. amd64 
docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t gcr.io/sound-helper-448209-a0/gradio-app:latest . 
#Uploading the image to GCR. 
docker push gcr.io/sound-helper-448209-a0/gradio-app 
#Deploying the GCR image to Google Cloud Run via command line. 
gcloud run deploy gradio-app --image gcr.io/sound-helper-448209-a0/gradio-app:latest  --platform managed --region asia-south1 --memory 4Gi --cpu 2 --timeout 3000s --port 8080 --allow-unauthenticated
